Step 1: Top-Down Design is a problem-solving approach where you start with the big picture and break it down into smaller, more manageable problems or tasks. These tasks are often called milestones. Helps organize your thoughts and plan your project efficiently.
Makes complex projects more manageable by focusing on one small problem at a time.
Allows for easier testing and debugging of individual components.

